Very compelling story. Very macabre. Challenging puzzles, wonderful art style. My only complaint was that it's a bit too short so the replay value isn't really there. Still, if you like point and click adventures, this one is certainly worth your time.

Yes, at first I didn't like it as it was quite different and I found the controls a nightmare! Not sensitive enough or something, I don't know, but picking up items and moving from scene to scene I found frustrating. I had to keep tapping the same area until it finally did something. Anyway, I'm not sure if I just got the hang of the controls or they did become easier, but I enjoyed it after a while. Challenging puzzles, no HOS, which was cool. Give it a try. Make more like this please.
